article.headline: Cornell 56, Columbia 51
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Ryan Wittman scored 15 points, including a 3-pointer to seal the win, as Cornell rallied in the final minutes to beat Columbia 56-51 on Saturday in the Ivy League. Louis Dale scored 13 points for Cornell (10-8, 3-1), and Andrew Naeve had 11 points and 11 rebounds. The Big red shot 44 percent from the floor, while holding the Lions to 34 percent shooting. Columbia (10-8, 1-3) was led by John Baumann with 12 points and 12 rebounds. Joseph Bova scored 10 points.
